sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Main as main.cpp (Thread)
    participant N0 as Honest Node 0 (C++ Object)
    participant S0 as gRPC Server 0
    participant N9 as Idle Node 9 (C++ Object)
    participant C9 as gRPC Client 9

    Note over Main: Initialization Phase
    Main->>N0: new Node("Honest_0", port: 50050)
    Main->>N9: new Node("Idle_9", port: 50059)
    Main->>S0: run_grpc_server(N0, 50050)
    Note over S0: Server 0 binds to port and listens
    
    Note over Main: Coinbase Generation (Act 1)
    Main->>Main: Create GeneratedTransaction (Coinbase)
    Main->>N0: add_transaction_to_mempool(coinbase)
    Main->>N0: mine_block()
    Note over N0: Performs SHA-256 Proof of Work loop
    Note over N0: Mempool cleared. Genesis Block & Block 1 saved to local std::vector chain
    
    Note over Main: Mining Race (Act 2)
    Main->>Main: Create GeneratedTransaction (Alice -> Bob)
    Main->>Main: simulate_mining_race()
    Note over Main: Honest_0 wins the race
    Main->>N0: add_transaction_to_mempool(tx)
    Main->>N0: mine_block()
    Note over N0: Block 2 saved to local chain
    
    Note over Main: Eventual Consistency Sync
    Main->>C9: new NodeClient(target="0.0.0.0:50050")
    Main->>N9: get_chain_length()
    N9-->>Main: length = 1
    
    Main->>C9: get_blockchain(start_index = 1)
    Note over C9: Serializes C++ int into Protobuf GetBlockchainRequest
    C9->>S0: [HTTP/2 Network Call] GetBlockchain RPC
    Note over S0: Deserializes Protobuf request
    
    S0->>N0: get_chain()
    N0-->>S0: Returns std::vector<BlockData>
    Note over S0: Serializes C++ structs into Protobuf GetBlockchainResponse
    S0-->>C9: [HTTP/2 Network Call] Returns Response
    Note over C9: Deserializes Response back to C++ std::vector<BlockData>
    C9-->>Main: Returns missing blocks
    
    loop For each missing block
        Main->>N9: add_block(block)
    end
    Note over N9: Node 9 is now perfectly synchronized!
